task.summary: Adds Files for assignment 1 in Data Structures Book - abstract parent to define the idea of a book - ReferenceBook - class for a type of book which cannot be borrowed and is locked to 1 quantity - FictionBook - type of book which is of the fiction genre - NonFictionBook - type of book which is of the Non Fiction genre Library - class to hold storage of Books with logic to support Assign1 - class to hold main method
Some cleanup for Assignment 01 removed useless methods Book.addBook, Book.inputCode added JUnit tests for Library and Book class
Sends entire module to git, mainly unversioned files adds JavaDoc files for Assignment 1
It all done :) added 2 text files for testing with assignment 2 added test module for random testing things without going to a REPL fixed various things in library such as read/write and addinorder

Final touches to Assignment 2 everything now works smoothly, only real changes: - changed topic to edition for referenceBook - added overloaded toString for NonFictionBook - added printing to Library.findBook

Added Lab 4, a sorting based lab - Sorts.java, a utility class containing static methods for - bubble sort = Sorts.bulbaSaur - insertion sort = Sorts.insertionSort - selection sort = Sorts.selectionSort - quick sort = Sorts.quickSort - merge sort = Sorts.mergeSort - trim zeroes = Sorts.trimZeroes A method to remove hanging zeroes from a primitive int array - Searches.java, a utility class containing static methods for - binary search = Searches.binarySearch - linear search = Searches.linearSearch - TestSearchSort.java a main class to run code Including javadocs for all the above classes and methods
Just some quick cleanups to all the files in Lab4 - adjusted whitespaces between some code blocks
ok finally. final final changes to lab04 had to fix the binary search algorithm changed calculation for time in main for the searches
final final final change to lab04 changed random to SecureRandom

final final final final changes to lab04 James wants this done in an incredibly stupid way so I had to change it to accommodate - when trying to sort/linear search before initializing array, now initializes implicitly instead of warning user - when trying to binary search array, will implicitly fill and/or sort array as needed - sub menu to choose which sort to do now repeats until user wants to exit back to main menu - SortingAlgorithms.java is now no longer abstract and has <T extends Comparable> in the class def, despite not doing anything with generics inside the actual class - main now prints out randArr and/or sortedArr whenever needed (because why yes, the user does in fact want to read through every single element of a 1000 length array every single fucking time they want to do something with it)
